title: Lauren Bushnell Celebrates Ben Higgins' Birthday With Sweet Post: 'I'm So Thankful For This Life Together'
text: Lauren Bushnell Celebrates Ben Higgins' Birthday With Sweet Post: 'I'm So Thankful For This Life Together' by Jennifer Drysdale 12:55   Photo: Instagram Lauren Bushnell and Ben Higgins are still going strong! The Bachelor couple proved their love for each other on Thursday, as Bushnell   wish her "babe" a happy birthday. EXCLUSIVE: Ben Higgins and Lauren Bushnell Talk Life as a 'Normal Couple' After Reality TV "Happy birthday babe I'm so thankful for this life together. Although sometimes rocky you always hold my hand and support me through it, always with a smile on your face," she sweetly wrote alongside a photo of the pair posing with a horse. "You deserve the world, especially today." A post shared by Lauren Bushnell (@laurenbushnell) on Mar 23, 2017 at 7:50am PDT EXCLUSIVE: Ben Higgins on Living and Working With Lauren Bushnell: 'It Isn't Healthy' ET caught up with Bushnell and Higgins earlier this month, where they opened up about living their life off-camera after the season finale o f Ben and Lauren: Happily Ever After? "A lot of people have been asking, 'Has life slowed down?' It hasn't really slowed down [but] we both feel a lot less stressed!" Bushnell revealed. "I feel like we're living life, enjoying, traveling just as much, but there's a lot less stress. We've adapted to this new lifestyle. We've learned a lot about each other -- what to do, what not to do, what makes each other mad, what makes each other happy." "I feel like we're finally just in a really solid place, in a good place maybe to start some wedding planning," she said, before adding that they have "no wedding updates." "But things are going well. I feel like we're in a really good place. We're having fun," she shared. "I think Lauren would love to move to L.A.," Higgins added. "[But] Denver is home for right now. My job is in Denver, our life is in Denver. Life has been crazy for the last two years, who knows what's next?" See more on the couple's life in Denver in the video below. RELATED SLIDESHOW
